MO FOX GIVIN showed early speed four deep then moved into the three path chasing the leader on the first turn, drew alongside to pressure the pacesetter, chased that rival leaving the backstretch, re-bid and dueled around the far turn, led into the stretch, overtaken by the winner at the eighth pole and got edged for second. UNCHARTED vied between briefly then ceded command but started to pull in the two path then between rivals on the clubhouse turn, continued two wide into the far turn, spun four wide into the lane and lacked the needed late kick in the furlong grounds. ACE OF CLUBS stalked along the inside, angled three wide on the far turn, got boxed in through the lane and never found room. ULTRA POWER showed speed three deep then took control and angled over to the inside on the first turn, pressured on the backstretch before moving clear again at the seven-sixteenths pole, challenged again by MO FOX GIVIN on the far turn, lost command leaving that bend and weakened down the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNQUESTIONABLE (FR) took a stalking position along the inside, coaxed along on the far turn, tipped two wide into the lane, bid three deep with a furlong left to run, gained the lead at the sixteenth pole and drove clear. MOUNTAIN BEAR (IRE) came away slow, traveled two wide outside a rival at the back early, on the move on the far turn, swung seven wide into the lane, closed well and got up for second, pulled up after the race and was vanned off. MY BOY PRINCE closest in pursuit in the two path early, bid from outside at the seven-sixteenths pole, dueled into the lane, took over in upper stretch, lost command with a sixteenth to go and got edged for the place honors. CAN GROUP broke a step slow, rank early on the inside at the back, swung six wide into the lane and summoned a mild rally for a minor award. AGATE ROAD traveled between rivals then moved over to the inside early traveling off the pace, remained inside then tipped to the two path on the far turn, went between rivals in the stretch, got brushed near the eight pole and improved position. TOK TOK reserved early and moved inside, roused on the far turn continuing to save ground, drifted out and brushed rival near the eighth pole and kept on between late. AIR RECRUIT sped to the front from inside, pressured into the far turn, came under a ride past the five-sixteenths pole, lost command with a furlong remaining, fought on to the sixteenth pole and weakened late. ENDLESSLY stalked the pace outside a pair of rivals, remained three deep on the far turn, entered the stretch four wide and failed to respond. CARSON'S RUN traveled three then two wide around the first turn, altered out past the five-sixteenths pole, angled six wide into the stretch, drifted inward in the lane and failed to threaten. STAY HOT stalked in the two path then between rivals, chased three wide into the lane and weakened. FULMINEO content to sit off the pace and traveled outside a rival, drew closer under urging and came five wide into the lane, found traffic at the eighth pole and weakened.
